n; the republicanisms of Bruce Ackerman and Cass Sunstein; and the originalisms of Raoul Berger, Robert Bork, and Keith Whittington. In so doing, this book provides a useful introduction to recent debates in constitutional theory and also contributes to the broader discussion about the proper role of the courts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aConstitutional lawzUnited StatesxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerzUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : Constitutional Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh1 aBrubaker, Stanley C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastillo, Cecilia R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDevins, Neal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolove, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagel, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeretti, Terri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, Christopher J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTushnet, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Kenneth D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Kenneth D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWhittington, Keith E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791482773423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791482773/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles